      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic model with isotropic hardening selected; justification provided that titanium alloy pedicle screw behavior under quasi-static bending is adequately captured by this model form.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw and UHMWPE block modeled with elastoplastic constitutive relations. Literature review confirmed isotropic hardening captures monotonic compression-bending response. Geometric nonlinearity (large deformation) enabled to capture post-yield behavior at 40 mm displacement. Model form assessed as adequate for the COU."
