      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to clinical failure modes (fatigue crack initiation, construct loosening) and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the FDA guidance for pedicle screw mechanical testing. Each QoI maps to a clinical failure mode: stiffness to load-sharing and adjacent segment disease, yield force to intraoperative over-tightening risk, and force at 40 mm to post-yield fatigue behavior. Relevance confirmed."
