    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted based on documented rationale: ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardized test geometry and the regulatory context does not require multi-condition variation for this submission. All three QoIs satisfy pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval <1.96, percent difference <10%) across N=11 specimens at two independent laboratories. The FEA model ensemble is assessed as credible for the stated COU. Note: this package was generated under ProfileMinimal; the signature workflow is pending and the signature field is absent pending completion of the organizational signing process.",
